      <p>The<italic>Journal of Business</italic>editorial board is pleased to announce the winners of the Merton Miller Prize for 2000. The winning article is “<ext-link ext-link-type="uri"
                   xlink:href="/cgi-bin/resolve?JBv73p287PDF"
                   xlink:type="simple">Managerial Decisions and Long‐Term Stock Price Performance</ext-link>,” by Mark L. Mitchell and Erik Stafford. The article appeared in the<italic>Journal of Business</italic>, volume 73, no. 3, July 2000.</p>
      <p>Awarded annually to the author(s) of the article agreed upon by the editorial board as the most significant to be published in the<italic>Journal</italic>in the preceding year, the $8,000 prize is funded jointly through the generosity of an anonymous donor and the Polaris Securities Group, Taipei, Taiwan, Republic of China.</p>
